additional_info:
First release. I will try to monitor any changes to SEIS that might make this obsolete.

For widescreen monitors use this:

@import url('data:text/css;base64,') screen and (min-width:1320px);
@import url('data:text/plain;base64,') screen and (max-width:1319px);


Unfortunatly, userstyles does not allow @import, even though this isn't hitting a server.

css:
@namespace url(http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml);

@-moz-document domain("www.seis.org") {

#forms-list-menu *
{
width:100% !important;
}


#outer
{
top:50px !important;
}

#inner
{
position:relative;
top:-50px ;
}

#forms-list-menu H2
{
font-size:2em !important;
}


#context-nav:first-child  td
{
display:none;
}

#context-nav:first-child  td:nth-of-type(2)
{
display:block;
}

#context-nav:first-child  td:nth-of-type(2) *
{
display:block;
}


#menulist-nav
{
display:none;
}


ul#menulist li {
display:inline !important;
float:left;
margin:.5em; important;
font-weight:normal !important;
clear:none;
width:auto !important;
}



#forms-list-submenu
{
display:inline;
}

#forms-list-submenu td
{
display:inline;
}

ul#menulist {display:block !important;

position:relative !important;
padding:0em !important;
margin:0em !important;
border:none !important;
}


#outer
{
position:relative;
}

}
